The '''amendment to the Security Act''' was a piece of legislation passed by the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Galactic Senate]] as an  amendment to the [[Galactic Constitution/Legends|Galactic Constitution]] that was voted by a wide margin the day after the [[Battle of Coruscant/Legends|Battle of Coruscant]].

==History==
It nominally transferred command of the [[Jedi High Council/Legends|Jedi High Council]] from the Senate directly to the [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]], thus providing him with the powers from the [[Galactic Constitution/Legends|Galactic Constitution]] to disband the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]]. It also removed Jedi and the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Galactic  Senate]] oversight of the [[Republic Military/Legends|Republic Military]], placing the chancellor in direct command as [[Supreme Commander (Republic)|Supreme Commander]].

It was written by [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] but given to a loyal [[Senator/Legends|senator]] to introduce, in order to maintain the façade of the Senate forcing power on him against his will.

